problems.title: Print Natural Numbers
problems.description:
Write a program to print all natural numbers from 1 to n using a while loop.

Input Format:
A single integer n.

Output Format:
Print numbers from 1 to n, each on a new line.
problems.examples:
Sample Input
5

Sample Output
1
2
3
4
5

Explanation:
Numbers from 1 to 5 are printed.
hintsList: Use a while loop to print the counter and increment it until it reaches n.

problems.title: Print Natural Numbers Reverse
problems.description:
Write a program to print all natural numbers in reverse from n to 1 using a while loop.

Input Format:
A single integer n.

Output Format:
Print numbers from n to 1, each on a new line.
problems.examples:
Sample Input
5

Sample Output
5
4
3
2
1

Explanation:
Numbers from 5 to 1 are printed.
hintsList: Initialize a counter variable to n.
Use a while loop to print the counter and decrement it until it reaches 1.

problems.title: Print Alphabets
problems.description:
Write a program to print all alphabets from a given starting character to an ending character using a while loop.

Input Format:
Two characters separated by a space.

Output Format:
Print characters from start to end, each on a new line.
problems.examples:
Sample Input
a e

Sample Output
a
b
c
d
e

Explanation:
Alphabets from a to e are printed.

hintsList: Initialize a char variable to start.
Use a while loop to print and increment the char until it reaches end.

problems.title: Print Even Numbers
problems.description:
Write a program to print all even numbers between 1 to n using a while loop.

Input Format:
A single integer n.

Output Format:
Print even numbers from 1 to n, each on a new line.
problems.examples:
Sample Input
10

Sample Output
2
4
6
8
10

Explanation:
Even numbers between 1 and 10 are printed.
hintsList: Check if the counter is divisible by 2.
Increment the counter in a loop.

problems.title: Print Odd Numbers
problems.description:
Write a program to print all odd numbers between 1 to n using a while loop.

Input Format:
A single integer n.

Output Format:
Print odd numbers from 1 to n, each on a new line.
problems.examples:
Sample Input
10

Sample Output
1
3
5
7
9

Explanation:
Odd numbers between 1 and 10 are printed.
hintsList: Check if the counter is not divisible by 2.
Increment the counter in a loop.
